headline: A Day in the Life of a Pool-Chair Policeman
summary: KAANAPALI BEACH, Hawaii—Tom Cooper stopped midsentence when he heard the clack clack clack of a metal lounge chair shifting into prime sunbathing position.  Cooper, age 56, swiveled his head toward the lower pool deck at  Marriott  Maui Ocean Club.
